How can we modify the ending of this Java code to create a new twist on the classic fairytale? 
```
public class PrincessStory {
   public static void main(String[] args) {
      boolean curse = true;
      boolean frog = true;
      boolean fog = true;
      boolean prince = true;
      while (curse) {
         if (frog && fog) {
            System.out.println("The curse is lifted!");
            prince = false;
            break;
         }
         else {
            System.out.println("The princess must find a frog and kiss it in the fog.");
            break;
         }
      }
      if (!prince) {
         System.out.println("The princess and her true love lived happily ever after.");
      }
      else {
         System.out.println("The prince was not meant to be her true love after all.");
         // Your code here
      }
   }
}
```

To add a new twist to the classic fairytale ending in the Java code, you can modify the ending so that the princess discovers a new path or revelation instead of the traditional "happily ever after" with a prince. Here's one way to do it:

```java
public class PrincessStory {
   public static void main(String[] args) {
      boolean curse = true;
      boolean frog = true;
      boolean fog = true;
      boolean prince = true;
      while (curse) {
         if (frog && fog) {
            System.out.println("The curse is lifted!");
            prince = false;
            break;
         }
         else {
            System.out.println("The princess must find a frog and kiss it in the fog.");
            break;
         }
      }
      if (!prince) {
         System.out.println("The princess and her true love lived happily ever after.");
      }
      else {
         System.out.println("The prince was not meant to be her true love after all.");

         // New twist: The princess realizes her true calling
         System.out.println("The princess embarked on a journey of self-discovery.");
         System.out.println("She traveled the world, helping those in need and finding happiness in her adventures.");
         System.out.println("Eventually, she became known as the wise queen who brought peace to the land.");
      }
   }
}
```

In this version, instead of being tied to the prince, the princess discovers her own strengths and purpose, leading to a fulfilling life full of adventures and wisdom. This adds a modern twist to the traditional tale, emphasizing personal growth and independence.
